    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Intake, Inlet, and Exhaust
        Manifolds - Installation - Exhaust Manifold
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Exhaust Manifold</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0608" count="1">Assemble exhaust manifold by inserting front and rear exhaust manifold sections
                into the exhaust manifold center section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place exhaust manifold gasket on assembled exhaust manifold and insert one exhaust manifold
                bolt in each end of the assembly. This will help align the exhaust manifold and gasket during
                installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350006173" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk14/K14008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Exhaust manifold</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 40 stud bolt (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 40 bolt (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 70 EGR cooler bracket bolt holes</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install assembled exhaust manifold and gasket onto cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install five M12 x 40 stud bolts and five M12 x 40 bolts finger tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_136.xml" xrefid="s0515">exhaust side EGR cooler bracket</hotlnk>
                and two M12 x 70 bolts
                <xref refid="s0515"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350006172" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK14/K14001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Exhaust manifold torque sequence</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0608.1" count="1">Torque 12 exhaust manifold bolts in the following three step sequence.</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts in sequence 1 through 12 to 27 N&#183;m (20 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts in sequence 1 through 12 to 54 N&#183;m (40 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts in sequence 1 through 12 to 105 N&#183;m (77 lbf&#183;ft).</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f066" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK14/K14009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EBP tube assembly and front exhaust manifold heat shield</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 12 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EBP tube nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 nut (3)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install front exhaust manifold heat shield on exhaust manifold studs and install three M8
                nuts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten three M8 nuts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install EBP tube nut into exhaust manifold and finger tighten.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M6 x 12 bolt through the EBP tube clamp and finger tighten.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten EBP tube nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten M6 x 12 bolt to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
